main event: Multiple UFO sightings were reported in Redlands, California, on various dates in 1956, 1958, and 1959, involving observations of saucer-shaped objects moving at high speeds and changing colors. In one instance, a photograph of an irregular, unidentified object approximately 30 feet in diameter was obtained. Another report described a bright, round, orange-colored object observed by multiple witnesses, which then changed color and accelerated rapidly before disappearing.
interesting points: A photograph of an irregular, unidentified object approximately 30 feet in diameter was obtained during one of the sightings.
Observers reported seeing saucer-shaped objects moving at high rates of speed and at low altitudes, with some objects appearing to hover and change colors.
The sightings involved credible witnesses, including an electrician in Redlands, California, and Mr. and Mrs. Walter Sanders who observed a bright, round, orange-colored object.
One report indicated that observers first saw the object when the film was developed, leading to a contradiction and rendering the sighting valueless.
The UFO report included details such as the time, date, location, exact latitude and longitude, and meteorological conditions during the sightings.
sighted object: various unidentified aerial objects, including saucer-shaped and irregularly shaped objects
witnesses: multiple credible witnesses, including an electrician and Mr. and Mrs. Walter Sanders
